headline: Has Rollins Recent Surge Left Limited Upside For Investors In 2025?
summary: If you are wondering whether Rollins is still worth buying after its strong run, or whether it makes more sense to wait for a better entry price, you are not alone. That is exactly what we are going to unpack here. Rollins has quietly kept rewarding patient investors, with the stock up 1.2% over the last week, 2.7% over the past month, 30.7% year to date and 29.6% over the last year, while delivering a 69.3% return over three years and 60.0% over five years. Those gains have been supported...
